@startuml
title Privacy Metadata Insights with Pegasus 1.5
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor #111111
  ArrowFontColor #111111
  LifeLineBorderColor #111111
  LifeLineBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  ParticipantBorderColor #111111
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #05D887
  ParticipantFontColor #FFFFFF
  ParticipantFontStyle bold
  ActorBorderColor #111111
  ActorBackgroundColor #05D887
  ActorFontColor #111111
}
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #F4FFF9
  BorderColor #05D887
  FontColor #111111
}
actor User
participant "Frontend\nMeta Insights Panel" as FE
participant "Flask API" as API
database "Local Cache\nPegasus Assist" as Cache
participant "TwelveLabs\nVideo Asset / Index" as TLIndex
participant "TwelveLabs Pegasus 1.5\nPrivacy Assist" as Pegasus

User -> FE: Click "Run Meta Insights"
FE -> API: POST /api/pegasus/privacy-assist/jobs\nvideo_id, local_job_id, force
API -> TLIndex: Load TwelveLabs video metadata \nand compute cache identity
TLIndex --> API: asset id and metadata
API -> Pegasus: Create analysis task\nmodel_name = pegasus1.5\nanalysis_mode = time_based_metadata
note right of Pegasus
Model
TwelveLabs Pegasus 1.5 reviews the indexed video for
privacy-risk segments, suggested redaction targets,
risk level, rationale, and time ranges.
end note
Pegasus --> API: task id
API -> Cache: Save queued job state
API --> FE: job accepted
FE -> API: Poll /api/pegasus/privacy-assist/jobs/{job_id}
API -> Pegasus: Retrieve analysis result
Pegasus --> API: structured privacy metadata
API -> API: Normalize, filter, and group privacy events
API -> Cache: Save privacy artifact
API --> FE: ready events, recommended actions, summary
FE --> User: Show privacy hotspots on timeline\nand grouped review actions
@enduml